## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="a8be6-113">Ten konstruktor tworzy odwołanie do reguły <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> obiektu zawierającego gramatyki.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a8be6-113">This constructor creates a rule reference to an <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object within the containing  grammar.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a8be6-114">Aby utworzyć odwołanie do reguły `rule` elementu w pliku gramatyki zewnętrznych użyć dowolnego z następujących konstruktorów:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a8be6-114">To create a rule reference to a `rule` element in an external grammar file, use any of the following constructors:</span></span>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef.%23ctor%2A>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef.%23ctor%2A>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef.%23ctor%2A>  
  
-   <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef.%23ctor%28System.Uri%2CSystem.String%2CSystem.String%2CSystem.String%29>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="a8be6-115">Poniższy przykład tworzy gramatyki, która rozpoznaje frazę "kraj, który ma won pojemnik World" następuje nazwa kraju, która została wybrana pojemnik World.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a8be6-115">The following example creates a grammar that recognizes the phrase "A nation that has won the World Cup is" followed by the name of a country that has won the World Cup.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a8be6-116">Po utworzeniu <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> obiektu `winnerRule` i nadanie mu identyfikator ciągu `WorldCupWinner`, przykładzie dołącza ciąg "kraj, który ma won pojemnik World jest" do reguły.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a8be6-116">After creating the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object `winnerRule` and giving it the string identifier `WorldCupWinner`, the example appends the string  "A nation that has won the World Cup is" to the rule.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a8be6-117">Przy użyciu <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> obiekty przykładzie następnie tworzy listę krajach europejskich oraz listę krajów Ameryki Południowej i dodaje każda lista do ich odpowiednich reguł `ruleEurope` lub `ruleSAmerica`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a8be6-117">Using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsOneOf> objects, the example then builds a list of European countries and a list of South American countries, and adds each list to its respective rule, `ruleEurope` or `ruleSAmerica`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="a8be6-118">Następnie tworzony odwołania reguły dla `ruleEurope` i `ruleSAmerica` i dodaje je do `WorldCupWinner` reguły.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a8be6-118">The example then creates rule references for `ruleEurope` and `ruleSAmerica` and adds them to the `WorldCupWinner` rule.</span></span>  
  
```  
public void WorldSoccerWinners ()  
{  
  
  // Create an SrgsDocument, create a new rule  
  // and set its scope to public.  
  SrgsDocument document = new SrgsDocument();  
  SrgsRule winnerRule = new SrgsRule("WorldCupWinner");  
  winnerRule.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
  // Add the introduction.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsItem("A nation that has won the world cup is: "));  
  
  // Create the rule for the European nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfEurope = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("England"),   
    new SrgsItem("France"), new SrgsItem("Germany"), new SrgsItem("Italy")});  
  SrgsRule ruleEurope = (new SrgsRule("EuropeanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfEurope}));  
  
  // Create the rule for the South American nations.  
  SrgsOneOf oneOfSAmerica = new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {new SrgsItem("Argentina"),   
    new SrgsItem("Brazil"), new SrgsItem("Uruguay")});  
  SrgsRule ruleSAmerica = (new SrgsRule("SouthAmericanNations", new SrgsElement[] {oneOfSAmerica}));  
  
  // Add references to winnerRule for ruleEurope and ruleSAmerica.  
  winnerRule.Elements.Add(new SrgsOneOf(new SrgsItem[] {(new SrgsItem   
    (new SrgsRuleRef(ruleEurope))), new SrgsItem(new SrgsRuleRef(ruleSAmerica))}));  
  
  // Add all the rules to the document and make winnerRule   
  // the root rule of the document.  
  document.Rules.Add(new SrgsRule[] {winnerRule, ruleEurope, ruleSAmerica});  
  document.Root = winnerRule;  
}  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="a8be6-119">Gramatyka utworzony ma następujący format.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="a8be6-119">The created grammar has the following form.</span></span>  
  
```  
<grammar version="1.0" xml:lang="en-US" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar" root="WorldCupWinner">  
    <rule id="WorldCupWinner" scope="public">  
        <item> A nation that has won the world cup is </item>  
        <one-of>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#EuropeanNations" />  
            </item>  
            <item>  
                <ruleref uri="#SouthAmericanNations" />  
            </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="EuropeanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> England </item>  
            <item> France </item>  
            <item> Germany </item>  
            <item> Italy </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
    <rule id="SouthAmericanNations">  
        <one-of>  
            <item> Argentina </item>  
            <item> Brazil </item>  
            <item> Uruguay </item>  
        </one-of>  
    </rule>  
</grammar>  
```

  
  
